Each wave, carrying the dense, decaying corpses of deities, surged towards the sky, relentlessly forcing the Punishing Heaven Alliance’s Crimson Bronze warships to retreat one by one. Some were completely shattered into countless fragments, falling into the boundless ocean of the universe below. The

number of Punishing Heaven Alliance members who perished in this fierce battle was considerable; even Jiang Mu Yang’s followers suffered tragic deaths, succumbing to the onslaught of the corpses. Those

far away, who hadn’t joined the battle and were still watching, including the powerful figures of the Lustful Heaven and Chaotic Heaven, were all shocked. They hadn’t expected this battle to be so brutal, that even the outermost regions of the ocean were inaccessible.

“Kill them! Charge!”

“With the Alliance Leader here, even if we die, we can be resurrected. Don’t be afraid, charge!”

Some people, fueled by the death of their comrades, became enraged and roared incessantly.

This kind of roaring resonated with many members of the delegation, as many believed Gu Changge was capable of anything, even the dead could be resurrected. The Punishing Heaven Alliance’s achievements in the Hall of Wrath could be exchanged for resurrection slots through accumulated points.

To this day, this belief still circulates within the Punishing Heaven Alliance, that even beings who died in the past could be resurrected. Suddenly, many were fearless, and even Jiang Muyang and a few others engaged in bloody battles, attempting to enter that massive tomb.

Here, the Crimson Bronze Ancient Warship emitted boundless auroras, the cries of “kill” resounded throughout the heavens, and all figures moved towards the depths. A dense mass of figures filled the sky, and fragments of light scattered everywhere, as if the heavens and earth were about to collapse.

In the boundless ocean of the universe, foam surged to the sky, seemingly capable of engulfing the entire cosmos. The eyes of all the worlds were focused on this scene, even the most desolate places of life were no exception.

Above the boundless cosmic sea, that vast, boundless tomb continuously solidified and drifted, exuding an overwhelming sense of oppression, as if an ancient universe was about to descend upon the world, falling from some dimension into existence. Terrifying fissures, densely packed, poured out an army of corpses—too many to count, densely packed, like dumplings floating beneath the surface, covering the entire high heavens.

The original, bloodthirsty members of the Punishing Heaven Alliance’s delegation, upon seeing this scene, couldn’t help but feel a little shaken and frightened, as if a beehive had been disturbed. This army of corpses, like a flood, was even more terrifying than the armies that had previously traversed the Ancient Treasure Civilization. In the

distance, the eyes of the Chaotic Six Paths were like lightning, seemingly able to penetrate everything, and he whispered, “With our strength, it’s almost impossible to cross. Even the Punishing Heaven Alliance members were stopped there.”

“It seems we still have to return to the realm and find more powerful experts to come here, otherwise we shouldn’t get involved in this mess.”

The Chaotic Heaven’s will personally issued orders, instructing them to go to the open sea, saying that this place contained the greatest secrets and opportunities since the creation of the world. This was even more tempting than the Hengtian Realm quota. However, at this moment, the Chaotic Six Paths hesitated, not daring to penetrate further. Hua Yueyong also said, “That’s right, how many past beings are buried inside that great tomb? That giant announced that there is a master inside, but we haven’t seen the so-called master appear yet.” “

And this is outside the front line of the ocean. Unless someone from the Punishing Heaven Alliance makes a move, but I heard that those from the Punishing Heaven Alliance have all disappeared. Could it be that we can only wait for that Alliance leader to

personally descend?” When mentioning “that Alliance leader,” a look of astonishment flashed in her eyes. It must be admitted that the prestige of the Punishing Heaven Alliance leader overshadowed all the countless realms and the Endless Space-Time universe. Even the Chaotic Heaven Will and the Lustful Heaven Will had to fear and be wary of him.

Just thinking about having the chance to see such an existence made her unconsciously close her legs.

“Well, let’s observe first.”

Lu Xun shook his head. Both of them only possessed the strength of the Lu Jin level, enough to stand proudly at the peak of the heavens in this current era, yet they still lacked confidence. This ocean was truly too strange.

Even the supreme beings in other realms, paying close attention to the movements on this ocean, were deeply shaken.

Some even spoke up: “The ocean is filled with endless mysteries, even the outermost regions are impenetrable. A powerful force like the Heaven Punishing Alliance, which destroyed the Ancient Treasure Civilization, nearly unified all the worlds, and even changed the ancient and modern cultivation methods, is now sending a delegation to the ocean, only to be thwarted like this. I wonder if this move will anger that powerful being?”

In this era, the Punishing Heaven Alliance exists, arguably supreme, unifying countless universes and spacetimes. Even other remaining forces and organizations can only hide like shadows, not daring to look directly at it.

But now, in the border region of the ocean, they have encountered setbacks, and many have realized that an unimaginable war is likely to erupt. The Punishing Heaven Alliance is very likely preparing for a prelude to war.

Boom!!!

In the boundless tomb realm, crimson lightning strikes down, piercing through the gloomy gray sky, accompanied by a torrential downpour of blood, submerging the cracked and fissured land. Such a scene is both bizarre and terrifying.

And in the depths of the ocean, many eyes, through secret techniques, are observing everything outside.

A towering, pure white structure, seemingly capable of purifying all the pale blue hues within, stood before a figure clad in a snow-white robe, his eyes a single white silhouette, silently observing and assessing everything. Finally, he murmured, “If the Bone Clan steps forward, perhaps they can withstand this storm. Otherwise, the tranquility of the Land of Creation will be shattered, and that eternal seal might be damaged again. Then, attracting the attention of the Land of Truth, the entire world will be twisted and turned upside down, everything overthrown and rebuilt.”

This place resembled an ancient city, with densely packed, towering pale blue spires standing one after another, their outer rings like clouds, resembling layers of jade belts, encircling the pale blue spires and leading them into the highest point of the sky.

As one observed downwards, one could see more and more blocks resembling tofu, moving back and forth along the incredibly wide and orderly narrow passageways of the architectural complex, bearing a style unlike that of the outside world. Dense, swarming creatures, like ants, busily lived within these structures. Many of these creatures were entirely white, as if solidified jade, their outer layers of clothing gleaming with a metallic sheen, carrying a strange order and rules. The

other side of the Food Pattern Tribe had confessed their guilt. A tribe member, claiming to possess a nearly original bloodline level, a similarly pure and white figure, walked to the highest pale blue tower and reported to the figure in the white robe ahead:

“So many years have passed, and the Food Pattern Tribe still has original bloodline members? And they’ve even awakened the ancestral patterns? It’s truly unbelievable. I thought having a fifth-generation bloodline with such purity would already be impressive.”

“This arrangement is perfect. You should have that member of the Food Pattern Clan sit in the empty Ming Cave and head towards the Unreturning Mist Sea. There are three Heavenly Dao Realm beings from the outside world there, attempting to forcefully break through. With the Food Pattern Clan’s ancestral script, which aligns with the unreturning heart, you can suppress those three Heavenly Dao Realm beings.”

The figure named Lord Wuxiang spoke, a crystal-like object floating high before him, radiating layers of shimmering light. Within it, the light flickered like a galaxy, seemingly reflecting many scenes from the outside world.

“Yes, Lord Wuxiang, I will bring it. However, judging from the current situation, there isn’t much activity in the Unreturning Mist Sea. Those three Heavenly Dao Realm beings probably won’t be able to get through .

