part of the Earth Vein has loosened slightly. I suspect that a wisp of the Earth Ancestor’s evil thought has escaped and gone to the outside world, leading to the current reversal of the great forces of heaven and earth. If we don’t stop it and stabilize the tranquility of the Land of Creation, and let the Land of Truth notice the abnormality here, the consequences will be unimaginable.”

“Yes, subordinate understands.”

This figure’s face became serious, not daring to say more, and hurriedly left.

“Punishment of Heaven Alliance? What kind of terrifying things have happened in the outside world? In the same era, breaking the constraints set by the will of Heaven, and simultaneously giving birth to three Heavenly Dao Realm experts, the future will probably be even more terrifying.”

“The Extinction Dao side has too much ambition; they might stir up trouble in the shadows, causing unexpected events to occur in the Unreturning Mist Sea. We must prepare in advance.”

The formless figure murmured, his face, devoid of any facial features, clearly showing signs of worry.

The Land of Creation is the vast land beneath their feet, existing since the birth of heaven and earth. To this day, it has experienced countless chaotic eras; in some ways, its history is even older than that of the Land of Truth.

Because the Land of Truth was founded by the three True Ancestors, it continues to expand to this day.

However, this Land of Creation predates the Land of Truth, existing only after the chaotic will was destroyed.

To put it simply, the ocean is not actually a static landmass; it is the place where the first and deepest of the 9898 paths of the chaotic will were received when the worlds of the universe were first created. Therefore, what remains here is not simply the remnants of chaos, but the slowly decaying “chaotic will” itself after its destruction.

It is simultaneously a world of decaying disease and a primordial womb, constantly distorting the reality of “Speaking the Truth” while silently nurturing new laws and embryonic forms. Of course, destruction also signifies rebirth; the initial chaotic will used to create all the forces of the vast universe dissipated here, ultimately forming the Creation Land. Within this Creation Land, due to the resources left behind by the “Chaos Will,” two completely different forces have developed. One is their Creation Alliance, which views chaos as the “Mother of All Things,” advocating the exploitation, integration, and even limited worship of chaotic legacies, from which they comprehend “forbidden laws” not permitted by the existing Heavenly Dao to create entirely new life and creation.

Therefore, the Creation Alliance has a very deep understanding and research of the Heavenly Dao Realm, even knowing how to break through under that kind of large-scale environment in the outside world.

However, it is precisely because this place lacks the authority of “Heavenly Dao’s will” that the Creation Land is merely a conceptual entity, unable to truly reach the Heavenly Dao Realm. Opposing the Creation Alliance is another force called the Gui Xi Dao.

The Gui Xi Dao sees the current chaos as a situation where it must be cleansed of the “Primordial Poison” master Zhang Zhe, the source of which must be decomposed, the forgotten remnants of chaos extracted from within, and used to repair the world’s “Dao damage,” ultimately restoring the ocean’s stability.

During this process, the Gui Xi Dao and the Creation Alliance constantly clashed in their ideologies, ultimately splitting and opposing each other deep within the Creation Land, creating the current estranged conflict.

Because of this ideological conflict, the “Earth Ancestor,” who was originally the will of chaos and had died, was also sealed in the darkness of this Creation Land.

The vast ocean outside, the Endless Mist Sea inside.

The Power Master, the Three-Headed Master, and the Qiankun Ancestor, along with the figure emerging from the depths of the vast mist, were locked in a standoff. A dense network of intricate lines and patterns, like a massive net, enveloped them. However, the three of them, emanating the aura of the Heavenly Dao Realm, resisted the net, preventing it from sinking even an inch.

The initially turbulent and turbulent mist sea gradually calmed down, becoming still and peaceful, as if no trace of anything had appeared.

“The Heavenly Dao Realm is indeed extraordinary; even this couldn’t suppress you. But this is only because the Endless Mist Sea hasn’t revived yet,”

the silver figure said, his tone filled with admiration and surprise. The bracelet in his hand continued to radiate boundless light, each ray and strand emanating downwards into the mist sea.It seems as though their wills are communicating within that same space.

The expressions of the Power Master, the Three-Headed Master, and the Qiankun Ancestor were all somewhat heavy. Even with their combined strength, they could only barely withstand that terrifying network of patterns. Any existence at the End of Realm level would be instantly trapped like a tiny worm in a spider web, unable to move. And that was only

because they were at the Heavenly Dao Realm. *Swoosh!!!*

Suddenly, a misty light rose, and a figure shrouded in a black cloak appeared. A black blade, carrying astonishing killing intent, slashed towards that silver figure.

This sudden scene startled the Power Master and the others.

“Returning to the Past…”

“You dare.”

The silver figure seemed not to have expected to be ambushed. Suddenly enraged, he reacted instantly, his bracelet flying out and continuously expanding, transforming into a shimmering, ancient starry sky, covering the attacking black figure.

“According to the rules, the Sea of Unreturning Mist is under the control of my Creation Alliance. You, the Sect of Returning Silence, have trespassed. Are you trying to break the rules? Are you trying to start another great war?” The silver figure

angrily spoke, his bracelet like the weight of countless armies, capable of crushing the heavens, thus suppressing and neutralizing the incoming blade of light. …

